'''Kadenokōji Akitomi''' (勘解由小路 在富) was a noble and {{ill|Onmyōji|ja|陰陽師|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of the {{ill|Sengoku period (Japan)|ja|戦国時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He held the Ranks of {{ill|Shōni|ja|正二位|1=Senior Second Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Hisanagi|ja|非参議|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and served as the head of the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Born as the son of {{ill|Kadenokōji Arishige|ja|勘解由小路在重|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, he was the last effective head of the {{ill|Kadenokōji family|ja|勘解由小路家|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Biography ==
Born to Kadenokōji Arishige and a daughter of {{ill|Machi Akiyuki|ja|町顕郷|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Akitomi was initially named Akihide (在秀). 

In {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 4 ({{ill|1507|ja|1507th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), he received the Rank of {{ill|Jugoi|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and was appointed {{ill|Hyōbu Shōsuke|ja|兵部少輔|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. By {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 9 ({{ill|1512|ja|1512nd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), he became {{ill|Reki Hakase|ja|暦博士|lt=Doctor of Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and in {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 11 ({{ill|1514|ja|1514th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), he was also appointed {{ill|Onmyō no kami|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He held multiple concurrent roles, including {{ill|Meryō|lt=Head of the Meryō|ja|左馬頭|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kunaikyō|ja|宮内卿|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

In {{ill|Kyōroku|ja|享禄|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 4 ({{ill|1531|ja|1531st year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), Akitomi reached the Rank of {{ill|Shōsanmi|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. For his close service to {{ill|Emperor Go-Nara|ja|後奈良天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, he was promoted to {{ill|Shōni|ja|従二位|1=Junior Second Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Tenbun 5|ja|天文5th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|1536|ja|1536th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), and later to {{ill|Seoni|ja|正二位|1=Senior Second Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Tenbun 20|ja|天文20th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|1551|ja|1551st year|qq=draft|qq=draft}})—a first for his family.

However, his sole son, {{ill|Kamo Akimasa|ja|賀茂在昌|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, fled Kyoto in {{ill|Eiroku|ja|永禄|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 2 ({{ill|1559|ja|1559th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) to study Western astronomy in {{ill|Funai|ja|府内 (豊後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and became a {{ill|Kirishitan|ja|キリシタン|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Left without a direct heir, Akitomi adopted {{ill|Kadenokōji Akitane|ja|勘解由小路在種|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, but their relationship ended in tragedy when Akitane was killed in {{ill|Tenbun 20|ja|天文20th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. 

Akitomi passed away on {{ill|Eiroku 8|ja|永禄8th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|1565|ja|1565th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}). The Kadenokōji clan faced further decline, leading to its eventual extinction.

