'''Kadenokōji Akitomi''' (勘解由小路 在富) was a noble and {{ill|Onmyōji|ja|陰陽師|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōji|qq=}} of the {{ill|Sengoku period (Japan)|ja|戦国時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sengoku period (Japan)|qq=}}. He held the Ranks of {{ill|Shōni|ja|正二位|1=Senior Second Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Second Rank|qq=}} and {{ill|Hisanagi|ja|非参議|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hisanagi|qq=}}, and served as the head of the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōryō|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=}}. Born as the son of {{ill|Kadenokōji Arishige|ja|勘解由小路在重|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kadenokōji Arishige|qq=}}, he was the last effective head of the {{ill|Kadenokōji family|ja|勘解由小路家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kadenokōji family|qq=}}.

== Biography ==
Born to Kadenokōji Arishige and a daughter of {{ill|Machi Akiyuki|ja|町顕郷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Machi Akiyuki|qq=}}, Akitomi was initially named Akihide (在秀). 

In {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eishō|qq=}} 4 ({{ill|1507|ja|1507年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1507|qq=}}), he received the Rank of {{ill|Jugoi|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jugoi|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} and was appointed {{ill|Hyōbu Shōsuke|ja|兵部少輔|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hyōbu Shōsuke|qq=}}. By {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eishō|qq=}} 9 ({{ill|1512|ja|1512年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1512|qq=}}), he became {{ill|Reki Hakase|ja|暦博士|lt=Doctor of Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Reki Hakase|qq=}}, and in {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eishō|qq=}} 11 ({{ill|1514|ja|1514年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1514|qq=}}), he was also appointed {{ill|Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Onmyō no kami|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyō no kami|qq=}}. He held multiple concurrent roles, including {{ill|Meryō|lt=Head of the Meryō|ja|左馬頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meryō|qq=}} and {{ill|Kunaikyō|ja|宮内卿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunaikyō|qq=}}.

In {{ill|Kyōroku|ja|享禄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōroku|qq=}} 4 ({{ill|1531|ja|1531年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1531|qq=}}), Akitomi reached the Rank of {{ill|Shōsanmi|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōsanmi|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Third Rank|qq=}}. For his close service to {{ill|Emperor Go-Nara|ja|後奈良天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Go-Nara|qq=}}, he was promoted to {{ill|Shōni|ja|従二位|1=Junior Second Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Second Rank|qq=}} in {{ill|Tenbun 5|ja|天文5年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun 5|qq=}} ({{ill|1536|ja|1536年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1536|qq=}}), and later to {{ill|Seoni|ja|正二位|1=Senior Second Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seoni|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Second Rank|qq=}} in {{ill|Tenbun 20|ja|天文20年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun 20|qq=}} ({{ill|1551|ja|1551年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1551|qq=}})—a first for his family.

However, his sole son, {{ill|Kamo Akimasa|ja|賀茂在昌|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo Akimasa|qq=}}, fled Kyoto in {{ill|Eiroku|ja|永禄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eiroku|qq=}} 2 ({{ill|1559|ja|1559年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1559|qq=}}) to study Western astronomy in {{ill|Funai|ja|府内 (豊後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Funai|qq=}} and became a {{ill|Kirishitan|ja|キリシタン|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kirishitan|qq=}}. Left without a direct heir, Akitomi adopted {{ill|Kadenokōji Akitane|ja|勘解由小路在種|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kadenokōji Akitane|qq=}}, but their relationship ended in tragedy when Akitane was killed in {{ill|Tenbun 20|ja|天文20年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun 20|qq=}}. 

Akitomi passed away on {{ill|Eiroku 8|ja|永禄8年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eiroku 8|qq=}} ({{ill|1565|ja|1565年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1565|qq=}}). The Kadenokōji clan faced further decline, leading to its eventual extinction.

